EXTRACTED VALUE: Compared to most movie-based video games, Robert Ludlum's The Bourne Conspiracy, sans Matt Damon, is a miraculous achievement in that it doesn't suck.
Despite the cutesy idea, there is a pretty solid game buried inside of Lego Indiana Jones.
It’s well put together, a joy to behold and a marvel to look at, but it’s just a lot of never ending sameness.
After her horrendous PS2 debut, Lara gets back into top form on the 360 with a back-to-basics exploration-based gameplay and tasty puzzles.
